procedures.name: Blood Sampling

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation, and pregnancy testing.

procedures.name: Urine Collection

code.decode: Volume measurement for timed collection, each

procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, drug screen, pregnancy testing, and 24-hour collection for copper and molybdenum content measurement.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Stool Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination

code.decode: Office or other outpatient visit for the evaluation and management of a new patient

procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and clinically significant findings.

procedures.name: Clinical Safety Laboratory Assessments
procedures.label: Lab Tests
procedures.description: Includes serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation, and urinalysis.

procedures.name: Urine Drug Screen

code.decode: Drug test(s), presumptive, any number of drug classes, any number of devices or procedures

procedures.label: Urine Drug Test
procedures.description: Screening for drugs of abuse in urine.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test

code.decode: Urine pregnancy test, by visual color comparison methods

procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine and/or serum pregnancy testing for females of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Collection and follow-up of adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs).

procedures.name: Height, Weight, and BMI Measurement
procedures.label: Anthropometric Measurements
procedures.description: Measurement of participant's height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Informed Consent
procedures.label: Informed Consent
procedures.description: Process of obtaining informed consent from the study participant.

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometry
procedures.label: ICP-MS Analysis
procedures.description: Laboratory analysis method to determine copper and molybdenum concentration in food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.

medicalDevices.name: Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

medicalDevices.name: Catheter
medicalDevices.label: IV Catheter
medicalDevices.description: A catheter may be used for venous access for blood draws, not to be left in place for longer than 72 hours.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure and Heart Rate Device
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead Electrocardiograph
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead ECGs.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively coupled plasma mass spectrometer
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Analytical instrument used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of samples.
